Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech at the U.S. Customs and Border Protection Advanced Training Facility in Harpers Ferry, West Virginia. He thanked Secretary Kirstjen Nielsen for her leadership and expressed gratitude to all the men and women of the Department of Homeland Security for their service. Pence discussed the challenges faced by law enforcement at the southern border, including illegal immigration, drug smuggling, human trafficking, and violence. He emphasized the importance of border security and praised the work of Customs and Border Protection agents. Pence also called on Congress to support President Trump's emergency declaration for border security and promised to work towards fixing the broken immigration system. He assured the law enforcement community that the administration will always have their back and thanked them for their sacrifices. Pence concluded by expressing his prayers for their safety and success in securing the nation.